^-{ ^*BDeal of the Week 351 - June 2, 2003^*N
 ^*BBy Fred Gitelman^*N }
^-
I had a new kind of victory last week. A team that my wife, ^*BSheri Winestock^*N, and me coached came second in the ^*BUnited States Women's Bridge Championships^*N thereby qualifying to represent the USA in the upcoming ^*BVenice Cup^*N World Championships. Congratulations to ^*BCheri Bjerkan^*N-^*BSue Weinstein^*N, ^*BStasha Cohen^*N-^*BPam Wittes^*N, and ^*BRenee Mancuso^*N-^*BBecky Rogers^*N!

Sheri and I are proud to have been the coaches of this team, but it should be noted that the material we used was created by my friend ^*BEric Kokish^*N. The teams that have been exposed to Eric's coaching program have performed remarkably well and the Bjerkan Team's qualification represents yet another feather in Eric's already feather-laden cap. Thank you Eric!

During the next couple of weeks we will be presenting ^*Blive^*N vugraph broadcasts of the ^*BSouth American Championship^*N, the ^*BCanadian National Teams Championships^*N and hopefully the ^*BUnited States Bridge Championships^*N (the team trials for America's 2nd ^*BBermuda Bowl^*N representatives). A schedule of these upcoming broadcasts can be found at:

