This week's deal was played by ^*BMarty Bergen^*N. Marty, a 10-time National Champion, was one of America's most successful players in the 1980s. However, Marty retired from active tournament play about 10 years ago. Since that time he has demonstrated that his talents for bridge go beyond simply playing the game as Marty has established himself as one of the most popular and prolific bridge writers in the world today.

Marty's books are intended for "average players" and they are filled with the wisdom that Marty gained during his distinguished career as a player. Marty has a gift for explaining important concepts in a clear and simple manner and his unique sense of humor really comes across in his writing. The bottom line is that "average players" will not only win more as a result of reading Marty's books, but they will find themselves entertained in the process.

Within the past year or so my company converted 2 of Marty's best-selling books, ^*BPoints Schmoints!^*N and ^*BMarty Sez...^*N, into interactive software products. For a limited time we are offering a ^*Bspecial^*N deal when people buy these products directly from us. If you buy either of these software products you will receive a ^*Bfree^*N autographed book by ^*BMarty Bergen^*N (an $8 value).

You can learn more about any of our software products and/or place an order through the following web page. Click on the blue rectangle below to go to this page in a new browser window:

